## Core Principles

### Clean Architecture
- Strictly adhere to the Clean Architecture layers: Presentation, Application, Domain and Infrastructure.
- Domain layer contains entities, repositories (interfaces).
- Application layer contains use cases.
- Presentation layer contains widgets, blocs, views.
- Infrastructure layer contains data sources, implementations of repositories.

### Feature-first Organization
- Each feature is a separate folder with its own widgets, blocs, views, repositories, use cases, and entities.
- Features are organized into a tree structure based on their dependencies.
- Features are independent and can be developed and tested in isolation.

### Project Structure
```
lib/
├── core/ # Shared/common code
| |__ config/ # Configuration, constants, environment variables
| |__ router/ # Router, navigation
│ ├── error/ # Error handling, failures
│ ├── network/ # Network utilities, interceptors
│ ├── utils/ # Utility functions and extensions
│ └── widgets/ # Reusable widgets
├── features/ # All app features
│ ├── feature_a/ # Single feature
│ │ ├── infrastructure/ # Data layer
│ │ ├── domain/ # Domain layer
│ │ └── presentation/ # Presentation layer
| | |__ application/ # Application layer
└── main.dart # Entry point
```
